ggests that the Galactic halo is more actively forming\nstars than previously thought and since most ECs do not survive the\n\\textit{infant mortality} it may be raining stars from the halo into the disc,\nand/or the halo harbours generations of stars formed in clusters like those\nhereby detected.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 3 Jul 2016 19:30:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
