gh $Rm$ therefore probably limits the relevance of the large-scale-vortex\ndynamo to astrophysical objects with moderate values of $Rm$, such as planets.\nIn this context, the ability of the large-scale-vortex dynamo to operate at low\nmagnetic Prandtl numbers is of great interest.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Jul 2016 11:20:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 31 Jan 2017 17:40:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-01"}
